Ground truth annotations are provided in JSON format, with bounding boxes around anomalous objects, labeled with track IDs, frame IDs, bounding box coordinates, and object types [thecvf](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFCYWDYUH0yRqOYXITW1TaAB8AzB1wJeMN0SRRW-tWLQMBQFF9O9IvS6B-qcLX-Ms75vbHCsUwK_yfp0mdnnXmVwptcnYIFqSOOhBMAl5Os_erPbZ6RgQEba1sfJfX0UF-sCKNDPw4YJunuK1O-KmyqLZicduxfC4kJ1fKU0b29E5IcqPkNgdytI4Ke-Epqb5kTqx608ixhUFyLQX3h0UTZfNRp2V1ZJf_0g1eaWZu2cnerSfEItxbak4mt2VCTosU=) [thecvf](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQNxIjfKZiayXwrq1NIV9Y_lPxxvqM7HAwIaXmBB6dcSR_mp1uyoHLSlLJighjMob8G2ef-w9p-to1kkhpccx7xcn7Ql5Io85Tu_WPcMXubxM7giX7tRKOrf8Hf2sboYogY-s2GiQE5E-GeQnpuV5pn8p4zvRsW0jHPOkHkHXDxsrBRv1nRqwsQvOa8BNpYBkJLwL-npKxKMNzHY5rYMqnFUoS0x49Yml3p75ok18BW9gOFEKqtc25l2DysAngFZXjSIo3_FQ=) [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGih42Z0yltnsNzOmxQvBHur-3xHc3HeBhLovw0DuFe0DEQsqGkxQudYRPsZ_BQrfLl7CwHZVlDkPJwNgR1DUJYKz-Pn2nhggZQZF3Hd4FKjN6F68Cc4Oeh4fk497w=) [zenodo](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGrLIBJJauDLUJjI2UTUXRg8JgelzQkfljBJRxQCNFayAg3rIV9Y_dBNipwXI0nqs3akxolCV0HSL-jeUf-3shlhMKOCTR-bm_oxrEXvlzwz28Vwu2G6irowuv8YaM=). It includes 35 human-related and 20 non-human-related anomaly types [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG1s8_KzlMSJa2_K5BPMUkokxpjwS7CzA5kABDGbBxkOKiODm5bTFT65tmz37jvRzA47M3G9KcQinoXvFFtdieU5OuHKOVU440Hrsq2qnq4Vs3TpbSB-tGH5I9I4hNu) [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEwk77EJnPr7u3SlRlsNNwDZynNLSx01wJyMzWFPVmPuBF4pQlsfyg2--Nfp52ap-ApmfezCA-HkDaLB4F7Z2LfEukHOPIRVrPFHyflWSNZBsjNDpTvZCzPTNIr8sb5ta3ul6QVmD6v]. During training, only video-level annotations are provided [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEBKPprZ1WKSIJsrxwaDJyQtyweR_R_Z3zhh9sufXdYxKhCDWl_nIHGUUgxuEc_qR9uiJNJibh_iaS9wHf62pnpGLFZN1QpnH_KtWIJIelFNYhLLi3drvZkcw==) [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHkwzAG-9C8s2m4PYd6GAFv1H5J9oS9xRzYCUBI51l0IT9iklq7ZXpTVHVzIcIsdVU-CseVdrUs4_SouvL9R0XSXwgliuAswuV15fvpShQt_0iYiB428RdiIUUd3Wo=] [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGq_9vvRbVonZZWE9OB1PqW3-a_DQ1kK6xPoNkmrYYDLyvbVyJEnr2epYcZZwSTLZI6yEWfRzL0eoIuCRXSGVlJZSBAroPodhfDVwe9PbCOudm273DjuRTcQ8ZKFrTK). To access the original video dataset, you need to submit a request through the application form on the project website: https://msad-dataset.github.io [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEIJzN4lkLF5A2jzvV-dRMPbdSZNB55jAp3g9EM1yaCbhwJsF2pkEVIlTOIoBtGSccNqj0k81ZjA6tHqiNmvnfM3ilzMiG7kYGTKUwRAM8GB1PYOmdhxUFThiW1nllZk4YgC4_l4TYj5EPasUZwUd4Z) [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGq_9vvRbVonZZWE9OB1PqW3-a_DQ1kK6xPoNkmrYYDLyvbVyJEnr2epYcZZwSTLZI6yEWfRzL0eoIuCRXSGVlJZSBAroPodhfDVwe9PbCOudm273DjuRTcQ8ZKFrTK).

4.  **NWPU Campus:** This dataset is designed for scene-dependent video anomaly detection and anticipation [computer](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFX08xQHecnpUFF0l-u-s_cXpMPf03GSioszMT12engv7SRyUn-_EvWR3P0d0cDvl_q589svPjTSfj_2jMP27Ac_xonr0sLL6GHpx-R5GRLVn8BHowg6XBY7Rrck82MnQSY1pPXHRgV3rj8XcYCNoLKqoxZ94btSp_WKpiydkpT4g==). It is available for download at https://campusvad.github.io [thecvf](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGH_nDRHlS1anU7y7KBWAQ8jrsaXSBrSh8inxMUJsa0io4JnOzzK2dWnTrmqQcIfdPtaFsSfP-qMsD6vsxd23fGnHuywkdsfLhYlBQfiv3ckLwMDoRbxU8e9k5l62Jz8kDtWtir7dEN-HNWu_tdfAWf13AoyNjrxeFeOD0gY7_6raHZAR3lWe0MeMlFW2vS1h6urYfUta5l73B0o1NNtzMvvNct74zHZ-7pjn-efl4uMmBnYofXvVBsc_IZDQxnVLo4f5JeKxmr_xSPTjA0GwjgHwKpdMV6) [paperswithcode](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGrLIBJJauDLUJjI2UTUXRg8JgelzQkfljBJRxQCNFayAg3rIV9Y_dBNipwXI0nqs3akxolCV0HSL-jeUf-3shlhMKOCTR-bm_oxrEXvlzwz28Vwu2G6irowuv8YaM=0) [mdpi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGrLIBJJauDLUJjI2UTUXRg8JgelzQkfljBJRxQCNFayAg3rIV9Y_dBNipwXI0nqs3akxolCV0HSL-jeUf-3shlhMKOCTR-bm_oxrEXvlzwz28Vwu2G6irowuv8YaM=1], and a GitHub repository is available at https://github.com/NWPU-Campus [github](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGrLIBJJauDLUJjI2UTUXRg8JgelzQkfljBJRxQCNFayAg3rIV9Y_dBNipwXI0nqs3akxolCV0HSL-jeUf-3shlhMKOCTR-bm_oxrEXvlzwz28Vwu2G6irowuv8YaM=2).

Okay, I will conduct targeted Google Searches to gather the most recent, credible information on "anomaly detection long-term video surveillance datasets labeled 2024-2025" and synthesize it into a verifiable text artifact.
Based on the search results, here's a summary of recent developments in anomaly detection datasets for long-term video surveillance, particularly those labeled in 2024-2025:

**Key Trends and Challenges:**

*   **Need for Comprehensive Datasets:** A recurring theme is the need for more comprehensive and diverse datasets to train robust video anomaly detection (VAD) systems [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [openreview](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). Existing datasets often have limitations in scenario coverage, motion dynamics, and anomaly types [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **Contextual Understanding:**  Real-world anomaly detection requires understanding context, such as time of day, day of week, and schedules [researchgate](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2) [thecvf](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).  Algorithms need to consider these contextual factors to accurately identify anomalies in long-term surveillance [thecvf](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
*   **Long-Tail Distribution of Anomalies:** Real-world anomalies exhibit a long-tail distribution, meaning some anomalies are rare, leading to data scarcity and challenges in large-scale data collection [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   **Privacy Concerns:** Collecting real-world anomaly data raises privacy concerns, hindering the creation of large datasets [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   **Evolving Definitions of Anomalies:** The definition of what constitutes an anomaly can change over time, even for a single camera viewpoint, requiring adaptable detection systems [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).

**Datasets and Benchmarks Introduced (2024-2025):**

*   **Multi-Scenario Anomaly Detection (MSAD) Dataset (2024):** This dataset comprises 14 distinct scenarios from various camera views, featuring diverse motion patterns and challenging variations in lighting and weather [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [openreview](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). It includes 35 human-related and 20 non-human-related anomaly types [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). MSAD aims to address the limitations of existing datasets by providing a more comprehensive benchmark for real-world multi-scenario video anomaly detection [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0).
*   **UCF-Crime-DVS (2025):** A novel event-based dataset for video anomaly detection using spiking neural networks (SNNs) [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5). It contains 1900 event streams across 13 anomaly classes, aligned with the original UCF-Crime dataset [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5). This dataset utilizes dynamic vision sensors (DVS) to capture visual information as discrete events, offering high dynamic range and temporal resolution [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5).
*   **SVTA (Synthetic Video-Text Anomaly benchmark) (2025):** A large-scale synthetic dataset for cross-modal anomaly retrieval, using generative models to overcome data scarcity and privacy constraints [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4). It includes 41,315 videos with paired captions, covering 30 normal activities and 68 anomalous events [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
*   **CamNuvem (2025):** A weakly labeled dataset focusing specifically on robbery events, containing 486 real-world surveillance videos from public sources [researchgate](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6).
*   **UCVL (2025):** A benchmark for crime surveillance video analysis with large models, including 1,829 videos and reorganized annotations from the UCF-Crime and UCF-Crime Annotation datasets [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7). It is designed to assess the ability of Multimodal Large Language Models to understand anomalous concepts [arxiv](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7).

**Algorithms and Approaches:**

*   **Trinity (2024):** A context-aware video anomaly detection algorithm specifically designed for long-term datasets. It is a contrastive learning framework that learns alignments between context appearance and motion [thecvf](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3).
*   **Deep BiLSTM Attention Model (2025):** An attention-based anomaly detection system designed to analyze spatiotemporal features and focus on long-term patterns [mdpi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).
*   **Approaches using YOLOv8 and CNNs (2025):** Integration of YOLOv8 and CNNs for real-time accident detection and vehicle number plate recognition [scitepress](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9).
*   **Meta-Learning Frameworks (2025):** Meta-learning frameworks are being explored for faster adaptation to new concepts in multi-scenario video surveillance [mdpi](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10).

**Key Datasets Mentioned (Beyond New Datasets):**

*   **UCF-Crime:** A widely used dataset consisting of 1900 long and untrimmed real-world surveillance videos with 13 realistic anomaly classes [paperswithcode](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11) [paperswithcode](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-12).
*   **ShanghaiTech:** Another popular dataset for anomaly detection in surveillance videos [paperswithcode](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11) [researchgate](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13).

This information should provide a solid overview of the current landscape of anomaly detection datasets for long-term video surveillance.
Anomaly detection in long-term video surveillance is a rapidly evolving field, with significant advancements in algorithms, datasets, and applications anticipated in 2024-2025 [openreview](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [forasoft](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2). This technology is crucial for enhancing security and efficiency across various sectors, including security surveillance, traffic monitoring, industrial monitoring, and healthcare [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [neurips](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1) [openreview](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).

**Key Concepts and Applications**
